## Key Lessons Learned

### Git
- Always `git pull` before `git push` to avoid conflicts
- Use `git commit --no-verify` to bypass Husky hooks
- Use `git remote set-url origin <url>` to fix wrong remote
- Force push with `git push --force` only when necessary

### Monaca
- Free tier has no GitHub push, no export
- Always use `config.xml` `<content src="...">` to set entry point
- Right-click `index.html` → "Open in Preview Panel" to preview
- Dev and Resume folders separate working vs production code

### Python/FastAPI
- Always use absolute file paths — relative paths break depending on where uvicorn is launched
- CORS must include all origins (localhost:5173 AND localhost:5500)
- Recreate venv if it disappears: `python -m venv venv && source venv/bin/activate`

### React/TypeScript
- TypeScript generics use `|` not `\` for union types
- `useState<Type | null>` not `useState<Type \ null>`
- Always check for uncommitted files before deploying

